<paragraph blockId="2.[151,739,1913,1939]" box="[151,739,1913,1939]" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,739,1913,1939]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,739,1913,1939]" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">
Redescription of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boulenger, 1888)" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[364,739,1913,1939]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Ptyas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[364,514,1913,1939]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">Ptyas doriae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[528,730,1913,1939]" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" refId="ref5551" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1888) An Account of Reptilia obtained in Burma, North of Tenasserim, by M. L. Fea, of the Genoa Civic Museum. Annali del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Genova, Series 2, 6, 503 - 604." type="journal article">Boulenger, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1984,2009]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="540" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[459,602,1984,2008]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Ptyas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[459,602,1984,2008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">Ptyas doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[649,870,1984,2008]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Cyclophiops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[649,870,1984,2008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="539">Cyclophiops doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation box="[922,1120,1984,2009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="539" refId="ref5551" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1888) An Account of Reptilia obtained in Burma, North of Tenasserim, by M. L. Fea, of the Genoa Civic Museum. Annali del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Genova, Series 2, 6, 503 - 604." type="journal article">Boulenger (1888)</bibRefCitation>
was brief and based on two specimens only. Also, a lack of knowledge of intrapopulational variation at the time probably led to the recognition of NHML 1946.1.5.32 as belonging to adifferent species by 
<bibRefCitation box="[843,1046,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refId="ref5604" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1900) Description of a new snake of the genus Ablabes from Burma. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 6 (34), 409. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930008678397" type="journal article">Boulenger (1900)</bibRefCitation>
. Subsequent treatments (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refId="ref6969" refString="Pope, C. H. (1935) The reptiles of China: Turtles, Crocodilians, Snakes, Lizards. Natural History of South Asia. Fol. 10. The American Museum of Natural History, New York, 604 pp." type="book">Pope 1935</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[224,357,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refId="ref7051" refString="Smith, M. A. (1943) The Fauna of British India, Ceylon and Burma, including the whole of the Indochinese sub-region. Reptilia and Amphibia, Folume 3, Serpentes. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, xii + 583 pp." type="book">Smith 1943</bibRefCitation>
) of this species were also very brief. Hence, a thorough redescription including an account of intrapopulational variation in lepidosis and colour description of this species is necessary. Here we provide a redescription based on our material (Appendix 1).
</paragraph>
